cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a modification to the MAML algorithm to handle tasks sampled from a multimodal distribution. The proposed algorithm is evaluated on diverse problems including regression, few-shot image classification, and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper also deals with reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics) and natural language processing, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
